BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:5549fa2e7c34368d1adce4f2ab1a94044c49beae@macro-calendar.local
DTSTAMP:20260528T170934Z
DTSTART:20260624T013000Z
DTEND:20260624T020000Z
SUMMARY:🔥 AU ABS: Barriers and Incentives to Labour Force Participatio
 n\, Australia
DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nReference period\n\nExplainer:\
 n• What it is: Employment / Payrolls / Labour Force\n\n• Measures: C
 hange in employment\, unemployment\, participation and labour-market str
 ength.\n\n• Usual market effect: Stronger-than-forecast jobs data is u
 sually bullish for the local currency and bearish for bonds if it increa
 ses rate-hike expectations.\n\n• Why traders care: Jobs data is a majo
 r driver of interest-rate expectations\, consumer spending expectations 
 and recession-risk pricing.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly.\n\n• Notes: For
  the US\, Non-Farm Payrolls is one of the most market-moving releases. F
 or Australia\, Labour Force data is important for RBA expectations.\n\n
 • Acronyms: NFP = Non-Farm Payrolls\; ABS = Australian Bureau of Stati
 stics\; BLS = Bureau of Labor Statistics.\n\nOfficial source: https://ww
 w.abs.gov.au/release-calendar/future-releases/202606
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT24H
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Tomorrow: 🔥 AU ABS: Barriers and Incentives to Labour Forc
 e Participation\, Australia
END:VALARM
