DTEND:20260731T020000Z
SUMMARY:🔥 AU ABS: Producer Price Indexes\, Australia
DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nReference period\n\nExplainer:\
 n• What it is: Producer Price Index\n\n• Measures: Change in prices 
 received by producers for goods and services.\n\n• Usual market effect
 : Higher-than-forecast PPI can be bullish for USD if traders expect prod
 ucer inflation to flow through to consumer inflation.\n\n• Why traders
  care: PPI can provide an early signal of inflation pressure before it r
 eaches consumers.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly.\n\n• Notes: PPI is usuall
 y less market-moving than CPI\, but it can still matter when inflation i
 s the main macro theme.\n\n• Acronyms: PPI = Producer Price Index.\n\n
 Official source: https://www.abs.gov.au/release-calendar/future-releases
 /202607
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
