DTSTART:20260826T013000Z
DTEND:20260826T020000Z
SUMMARY:🔥 AU ABS: Consumer Price Index\, Australia
DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nReference period\n\nExplainer:\
 n• What it is: Consumer Price Index\n\n• Measures: Change in the pri
 ces paid by consumers for a basket of goods and services.\n\n• Usual m
 arket effect: Higher-than-forecast inflation is usually bullish for the 
 local currency and bearish for bonds\, because markets may price in high
 er interest rates.\n\n• Why traders care: CPI is one of the most watch
 ed inflation indicators because it can quickly shift central-bank rate e
 xpectations.\n\n• Frequency: US CPI is monthly. Australian CPI has bot
 h monthly indicator releases and quarterly CPI releases.\n\n• Notes: C
 ore CPI removes volatile items such as food and energy to give a cleaner
  read on underlying inflation pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: CPI = Consumer 
 Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/release-calendar
 /future-releases/202608
