UID:47c4274647800928c84649eec207cb14a1be741f@macro-calendar.local
DTSTAMP:20260528T170934Z
DTSTART:20261125T133000Z
DTEND:20261125T140000Z
SUMMARY:🔥 US BEA: Personal Income and Outlays\, October 2026
DESCRIPTION:Source: US BEA\nImpact: high\nwww.bea.gov\n\nExplainer:\n• 
 What it is: Core PCE Price Index\n\n• Measures: Change in prices paid 
 by consumers for goods and services\, excluding food and energy.\n\n• 
 Usual market effect: Higher-than-forecast inflation is usually bullish f
 or USD and bearish for bonds\, because it can increase expectations of t
 ighter Federal Reserve policy.\n\n• Why traders care: Core PCE is one 
 of the Federal Reserve's preferred inflation measures\, so it can strong
 ly influence interest-rate expectations.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly\, usu
 ally released about four weeks after the month ends.\n\n• Notes: Core 
 PCE differs from Core CPI because it uses a different basket and weighti
 ng method. CPI often gets more immediate market attention\, but Core PCE
  is very important for Fed policy.\n\n• Acronyms: PCE = Personal Consu
 mption Expenditures\; CPI = Consumer Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: ht
 tps://www.bea.gov/news/schedule/ics/online-calendar-subscription.ics
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
